<br>
Who has one?<br>
<br>
What is your haste?<br>
<br>
Did it make a difference to you and the guild for tanking?<br>
<br>
How do you use it  (ie which combo do you use, or with which weapons do you use it for best results)?<br>
<br>
*I realize for some guilds who are at the end game there are much better toys out there, but let us speak of a guild which is pre-sleepers tomb, pre-NToV. <p><br><img src="http://www.havocink.com/eq/sig_tuggbar.gif" alt="Dirtnap, Inc.">


<CENTER><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59492" target="_blank">Tuggbar's Stash</a></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=surloksoulbain>Surlok Soulbain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/02 9:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=485.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Epic.</span><hr size=1> The risk is fairly minimal the biggest problem/reason the warrior epic is not made easier is because almost all of the peices are tradeable.How do you convince Verant that getting a green scale is too hard when you can just pop onto your one of your servers high end guild boards and ask to buy one? I personally do not have 60 k to buy one so I must hope that I can catch Sev and that he actually drops the scale.The rest of the peices are fairly easy to get ..last weekend in Fear we got 2 golem balls for the guild..red scales sell on my server for 5k so getting them is pretty simple if you missed out on naggy..<br>
<br>
The weapons are nice great if you are not an MA for doing Damage..Most warriors I have seen use the red blade in the offhand for the proc and use a frost bringer/willsapper whatever other good aggro weapon they can obtain until they replace both with even better... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/urobokeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RobokEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/02 9:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=485.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Epic.</span><hr size=1> For my guild warrior epics did help alot. When i first got mine most our warriors were using frostbringers etc and the taunt upgrade was awesome. <br>
<br>
It takes some work to get and there are other weapons out there that you could get that would do you just as much good if not more then epics (willsapper is fairly easy to get, dunno how strong your guild is, Eashen isnt too hard and claws of lightning make a good off hand).<br>
<br>
I used both epics and an RBB for haste right up untill i got primal, i still switch in my blade of strategy for a proc now and again.<br>
<br>
Its worth it if your willing to put in the work, for alot of warriors that means getting their guild to do VP because the green scale that drops there is far less contested. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11531"> -Robok- </a> <BR>
