</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaranaro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaranaRo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/02 10:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=485.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Epic.</span><hr size=1> Anyone using a Frostbringer in either hand over the warrior epic is a tard. And you can quote me.<br>
<br>
For one the Strategy blade proc is 100 DD (give or take resists) but has aggro as if it were a 500 DD. That alone makes it better in the mainhand than a Frostbringer.<br>
<br>
Secondly the Tactics blade worn effect adds 40 to dex, also adding to more procs. As an ogre I see a significant increase in procs/aggro gain from dual wielding my epic over my previous combo of Frostbringer/Ornate Sword of the General.<br>
<br>
My haste is 26% when not buffed in some form. (Siblisian Berserker Cloak)<br>
<br>
The only way I would trade out one of my epic blades is for something that would grant a significant increase in aggro like a Willsapper or something else along those lines.<br>
<br>
Anyone using a Frostbringer over either of the epic blades really and truly has no clue how to control aggro.<br>
<br>
I don't claim to be the best tank out there, in fact I know I'm not, but I know enough to not use an inferior weapon to my epics. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=56851>Daku Krugnak</a><br>59 Myrmidon<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=56844>Tarana Ro'Firehand</a><br>57 Evoker<br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77117>Imgunna</a><br>17 Monk<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77078>Tomalin Hafpint</a><br>35 Druid</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubouldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bouldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/02 2:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=485.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Epic.</span><hr size=1> Red epic makes a great off-hand.<br>
<br>
I use it offhand with Willsapper in main to maximize my aggro.<br>
<br>
Not only is the red proc 100dd plus extra hate, but it also has +15 stamina and 50hps. It's just a great weapon to use. One red proc, and the mob is on you like glue.<br>
<br>
Blue epic is so-so. The innate dex and attack buff is nice, but to me, the best warrior setup is a good hate proccer in each hand. Blue-bie gets bagged by me most of the time.<br>
<br>
I think the difficulty of the warrior epic has been somewhat overstated. As far as risk versus reward goes, to me, it's totally worth it. <p><img src="http://www.enjoyer.com/barrel.gif" width="270" height="150" border="0">
