Cloak of Flames - 36 percent (always also have SotS or AQ/VoG on guild raids)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Did it make a difference to you and the guild for tanking?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'd say it did. A long time ago (or so it seems), my guild had tried the Vindicator several times. By the time our three main warriors at the time finished our epics (in quick succession), we finally killed the Vindicator with combination of new found agro weapons on our main tanks and our new knowledge and tactics. We can now kill the Vindicator flawlessly, because of progression. We've since started moving onto other mobs. As far as the big mobs go, we've killed Rumblecrush, Cazic-Thule, the Vindicator, Velketor, Innoruuk, and Dozekar. All of these kills were with epic equipped warriors main tanks. I've also tanked the 425 dual wielding Dain great using my epic.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  How do you use it (ie which combo do you use, or with which weapons do you use it for best results)?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I primarily use the 2HS version personally. I only really use the 1HS versions when I'm not the first/only tank, and there are other epic warriors present. I'm aiming to get a Willsapper to pair with my Red Blade though for optimal agro, and a Primal Warsword for the proc. From what I've heard, that should work quite well up until you can get enraging blow weapons and the like. I'd really like that 2HS off Vyemm too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
