<br>
Red blade primary<br>
Blue blade secondary<br>
?<br>
<br>
Or<br>
<br>
Wavecrasher primary<br>
Red blade secondary<br>
?<br>
<br>
Been MT as long as my character has lived.  Currently using Wavecrasher and Frostbringer.  Never had any problems keeping aggro away from any epic wielders.  Even been in exp groups where I could see that the other warrior was &quot;trying&quot; to take aggro from me but couldn't, or I would very easily flip the mob right back to myself on any of his successful taunts (can see him getting all up in the mobs face, switching his red epic around, trying both epics, then red with some other faster weapon primary, etc.. he was obviously experimenting to see how he could steal aggro).  Only time a mob ever turned to them is when they would proc.  Most of the time I would turn the mob back right away, sometimes it would take a proc of my own if they had procced.<br>
<br>
But in my experiences so far, I'm not going to ge a huge aggro upgrade from epics.  Or &quot;will&quot; I?  Maybe it's just the way that I hold aggro, and not so much the weapon choice, and maybe the epics will just mean I have even better aggro.  I mean, discounting procs alltogether, an epic wielding warrior has &quot;never&quot; been able to take and &quot;hold&quot; aggro away from me.  I've always been able to hold it from them.  Adding procs back into the equation and there's a little more randomness on where the aggro can go... but for the most part, a worst case scenario I'd get it back when I procced as well (24 delay vs. 19 delay, I proc more on top of it).  Really, the only times that I wouldn't be able to hold aggro from an epiced warrior is if they chained a quick 2 or 3 procs, while I remain completely procless the entire battle.  If I proced at all, it would completely counter their procs and I'd have aggro.  If no procs came from either of us, I've got aggro the entire time as well.<br>
<br>
What would you all suggest?  Add the epic to my current setup?  Or completely replace my current setup with the epics? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umebe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/20/02 2:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=485.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Epic Use....</span><hr size=1> By the way, since this is an epic discussion: when you are not the MT, put the damned red blade away! No one else cares about the 15STA and 50HP when the mob is not hitting you and the mob should not be hitting you. 14/24 is a crappy ratio and even if you have to step down in damage output, one turn of the mob (and the missed backstabs that implies) probably more than makes up for the difference between you that 14/24 red blade and whatever else you have. <br>
